# 👨‍🏫 Mentor's Note

This lesson connects directly to something you pointed out around **Day 18**.

You said:

> *"In the real-time scenario in the app, we should not update the hemoglobin numbers. We have to store them as two different tests like Test 1 and Test 2."*

That was exactly the right way to think.

Today we've formalized that idea:

* **Never overwrite old test results.**
* **Every uploaded report becomes a new record.**
* **Each report contains its own set of blood test values.**

This allows users to see their health journey over months and years, which is one of the biggest strengths of your app.

